    "(3) Value alignment on human-annotated or AI-annotated preference dataset where humans' value is injected into the LLMs [1,2,39].Currently, these steps are mostly conducted on publicly available data, which is either publicly released [22,23] or AI-generated [40,16,41,42].",
    "However, it has been estimated that high-quality public data will exhaust before 2026 [13], indicating a forthcoming bottleneck of current LLMs since more data usually contributes to better performance [17].",
    "Therefore, recently, there have been several attempts that train LLMs on large-scale privately-kept data [4,43].",
    "For example, trained on financial data spanning 40 years, BloombergGPT [19] has demonstrated strong performance in finance.However, in the real world, the data amount of each party could be limited, while the union of massive parties' data could form a large database to train a powerful LLM [14].",
    "Therefore, it becomes imperative to contemplate the forthcoming evolution of LLMs: collaborative training on distributed private data in a privacy-preserving way."
  ],
